FBIS4-8848 "dreeu075_i_94008" FBIS-EEU-94-075 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Gorazde Situation Worsens as Attack Continues Serbs Call for Surrender LD1504202694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 2001 GMT 15 Apr 94 LD1504202694 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Sarajevo, 14 Apr (TANJUG) -- The supreme command of the Srpska republic armed forces this evening issued a statement calling on citizens of Muslim and Serb nationalities from the Gorazde area to take refuge behind the Serb lines, where they will be guaranteed security and protection. Full security and protection is also guaranteed to all members of military and police units who end attacks on Serb positions and surrender their arms to the Srpska republic army, reads a statement of the supreme command of the Srpska republic armed forces.
